# Nethereum's Online Testchain

In order to help developers test their code, Nethereum provides an online Testchain at  `http://testchain.nethereum.com:8545`.

This chain is based on a [Geth node](https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum) running clique-PoA as consensus, enabling fast response.

You can interact with Nethereum's Online Testchain using Ethereum's regular [JSON-RPC Api](https://github.com/ethereum/wiki/wiki/JSON-RPC#json-rpc-api).

Nethereum's Online Testchain resets every 10 minutes, this means it will accomodate short testing sessions, but the deployed contracts, balances and logs will be wiped out every 10 minutes. The advantage of this is that the pre-funded accounts (avalable for your use in the table below) get replenished constantly. However, for extensive testing sessions and persistent contract storage, we recommend checking our [list of devchains](choosing-a-chain-for-development.md).

If you would like to try Nethereum's Online Testchain without any setup, you can see it work on [Nethereum's Playground](http://playground.nethereum.com)
